1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:07,867
Kafka 2.8+ introduced KRaft (Kafka Raft) — a built-in consensus mechanism that eliminates the ZooKeeper dependency entirely.

2
00:00:07,817 --> 00:00:13,750
In KRaft mode, a quorum of broker nodes use the Raft protocol to manage cluster metadata directly.

3
00:00:13,750 --> 00:00:19,528
Real talk: Flipkart's Big Billion Day crashed their servers THREE times before they got this right.

4
00:00:19,528 --> 00:00:22,269
Product companies pay 30+ LPA.

5
00:00:22,269 --> 00:00:25,346
Service companies pay 3.3 LPA.

6
00:00:25,346 --> 00:00:26,528
The difference?

7
00:00:26,528 --> 00:00:28,682
Exactly what we're learning.

